TEXT(&beginproblem);
$showpartialcorrectanswers = 1;

$a = random(1, 12, 1);
$b = random(1, 7,1);
$c = random(.1,1,.1);

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
One hour after \(x\) milligrams of a drug are given to a person, the
change in body temperature \(T(x)\) (in degrees fahrenheit)
is given by the function
 \[ T(x) = x^2 (1 - \frac{x}{$a}). \]
Further, the rate \( T'(x) \) at which \(T\) changes with respect to
the size of the dosage, \(x\), is called the sensitivity
of the body to the dosage.  Find:
$BR
(A) \( T'(1) \) = \{ans_rule(40) \}
$BR
EOT

$ans = (2)*(1 - (1/$a)) + (-1/($a));
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
(B) \( T'(3) \) = \{ans_rule(40) \}
$BR
EOT

$ans = (6)*(1 - (3/$a)) + 9*(-1/($a));
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
(C) \( T'(6) \) = \{ans_rule(40) \}
$BR
EOT

$ans = (12)*(1 - (6/$a)) + 36*(-1/($a));
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ans));

